2.00	The_Planetworkshops	The Planetworkshops	The Planetworkshops are a think tank that combine reflection and action with the goal of promoting sustainable development and initiating societal transformations. The Planetworkshops were created in 2006 by Eric Bazin (founder of Satelight) and George J. Gendelman (former Director of the New York Times and of the International Herald Tribune).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/34/Logo_Planetworkshops.jpg/220px-Logo_Planetworkshops.jpg
